      • createUpdateBatch

        public static org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Bundle createUpdateBatch​(java.util.List<org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.DomainResource> resources)
        Creates a Bundle of type "batch" with an entry for each resource provided. Expects that each resource have an id, so that it can create a "request" with a method of "PUT resourceType/id" Example: createUpdateBatch(List.of(resource1, resource2, resource3))
        Parameters:
        resources - The list of resources to be added to the batch
        Returns:
        Bundle that can be executed as a transaction on the FHIR server

      • getPatientMeasureReportReferences

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> getPatientMeasureReportReferences​(org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.MeasureReport masterMeasureReport)
        Traverse each population in the measure report and find the subject results of the population, which is a reference to a contained List resource. The contained List resource contains each of the individual patient measure reports that is used to calculate the aggregate value of the population.
        Parameters:
        masterMeasureReport - The master measure report to search for lists of individual reports
        Returns:
        The list of unique references to individual patient MeasureReport resources that comprise the master

      • storeTerminologyAndReturnOther

        public static org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Bundle storeTerminologyAndReturnOther​(org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Bundle bundle,
                                                                          ApiConfig config)
        Creates a bundle of the same type as the measure definition bundle and another bundle of type batch, Then traverses the measure definition bundle, adding all the ValueSet and CodeSystem resources to the batch bundle and stores them on the configured TX server while all the other resources are added to the new measure definition bundle to be returned.
        Parameters:
        bundle - measure definition bundle
        config - contains Api configurations
        Returns:
        A bundle of the same type as the measureDefBundle bundle without any of the ValueSet or CodeSystem resources.
